cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically object counting. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel neural network architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing methods and proposes a new approach, which involves modeling the task as a closed-set problem. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper includes experiments on toy data, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
